[agent-review] details:
Narrative:
The diff is a single-line change bumping the Crucible timeout from 300s to 600s in the CLI's inline task builder. The model default (`CrucibleConfig.timeout`) was already updated to 600 in models.py (line 72), so this change simply brings cli.py in sync. The explicit `timeout=600` in the CLI is now redundant with the model default but is otherwise correct and harmless. No correctness, security, or invariant issues found.

Findings:
- [Info] factory/cli.py:134 Consider omitting the explicit timeout=600 so the model default is the single source of truth, or extract a named constant shared by both.
  description: CrucibleConfig in models.py already defines `timeout: int = 600` as the default (models.py:72). The explicit `timeout=600` in _build_inline_task is now redundant. If the default ever changes in the model, this call-site will silently override it, creating a maintenance hazard where two locations must be updated in lockstep.

