[agent-review] details:
Narrative:
The timeout increase itself is safe, but the change introduces/retains configuration inconsistency across task-entry paths and keeps a duplicated magic default in code. No security or performance regressions were found in the modified line alone, but architecture/API consistency can be improved.

Findings:
- [Warning] factory/cli.py:134 Align Crucible timeout defaults across inline builder and task templates (or document intentional divergence).
  description: Inline tasks now hardcode Crucible timeout to 600s, while checked-in YAML templates still explicitly set 300s. This creates API inconsistency: `factory run <inline prompt>` and `factory poll` without `--template` use 600s, but template-driven runs can still use 300s. The same feature behaves differently depending on task source, which is hard to reason about operationally.
- [Info] factory/cli.py:134 Remove duplicated literal timeout or centralize it in a shared constant/default path.
  description: The inline task builder hardcodes `timeout=600` even though `CrucibleConfig` already defines a default of 600. Keeping duplicated literals in multiple places increases maintenance overhead and can silently drift when defaults evolve.

